value.title: Appeals court OKs Trump taking military money for border wall
value.excerpt: A federal appeals court ruled Friday that a lower court was wrong to bar the Trump administration from taking $3.6 billion from military construction projects for a border wall.

value.title: Historians sue Trump administration to stop ‘bonfire of records in the Rose Garden’
value.excerpt: The American Historical Association and other groups fear President Trump, Jared Kushner, Ivanka Trump and others in his inner circle may not preserve critical records

value.title: Trump to withdraw most troops from Somalia as part of global pullback
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump has ordered nearly all American troops to withdraw from Somalia, U.S. officials said on Friday, part of a global pullback by the Republican president before he leaves office next month that will also see him drawdown forces in Afghanistan and Iraq.

value.title: Trump campaign paid Dechert $164K for 'recount' related legal services, FEC filings show
value.excerpt: U.S. President Donald Trump's campaign last month paid more than $164,000 to Dechert, a law firm that during the 2020 election touted its work on pro bono voting rights cases in which it often faced off against Republican-backed lawyers.

value.title: Lara Trump teases potential Senate run in North Carolina
value.excerpt: Lara Trump teased a potential Senate run in North Carolina Friday to replace Sen. Richard Burr, who is retiring after three terms in 2022.

value.title: MSNBC's Kasie Hunt panned for saying she's 'struck' how Biden 'as a rule, doesn’t lie'
value.excerpt: MSNBC anchor Kasie Hunt was widely mocked on social media Friday for being excessively trusting of President-elect Joe Biden.

value.title: California certifies Joe Biden’s victory, giving the Democrat more than the 270 electors needed to win the White House
value.excerpt: California certifies Joe Biden’s victory, giving the Democrat more than the 270 electors needed to win the White House

value.title: Consulting firm scrubs Wiki page of Biden’s COVID-19 czar: report
value.excerpt: The Wikipedia page for President-elect Joe Biden’s new Covid czar Jeff Zients has been scrubbed of material that could portray him as not progressive enough, Politico first reported.

value.title: Ousted cybersecurity chief Krebs to Trump: 'These constant attacks ... are very dangerous'
value.excerpt: Former top cybersecurity official Chris Krebs sent a clear message to President Donald Trump on Friday: Stop attacking the integrity of last month's election because American democracy is fragile.

value.title: President Trump’s niece, Mary Trump, says her ‘cruel and traitorous’ uncle belongs in prison
value.excerpt: Mary Trump rejects the notion that putting a former president on trial would deepen the nation’s political divisions.

value.title: Obama and Pence hit Georgia campaign trail to court Senate runoff voters
value.excerpt: "Anybody listening right now, you need to realize this is not just about Georgia," Obama said. "This is about America - this is about the world."

value.title: Trump administration must accept new DACA applications, judge orders
value.excerpt: The Trump administration must post a public notice that it will accept new applications for the Obama-era program shielding undocumented immigrants who came to the US as children from deportation, a federal judge ordered Friday.

value.title: Nissan joins GM in exiting auto group backing Trump
value.excerpt: Japanese automaker Nissan Motor Co said on Friday it was joining General Motors in exiting a group of automakers that had backed U.S. President Donald Trump in his bid to prevent California from imposing its own vehicle emissions rules.

value.title: Trump purges Pentagon advisory board and gives seats to former campaign managers
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump has purged a Pentagon business advisory board and replaced its members with his former campaign manager and deputy campaign manager, neither of whom have served in the military or have any apparent experience with the defense industry.

value.title: Trump administration appoints loyalists Corey Lewandowski and David Bossie to Defense Business Board
value.excerpt: The Trump administration installed loyalists on a Pentagon advisory panel on Friday, naming Corey Lewandowski and David Bossie among the new appointees to the Defense Business Board. The appointments were announced along with the removal of other members,

value.title: Trump to award wrestling legend Dan Gable the Presidential Medal of Freedom
value.excerpt: President Trump will award Olympic gold medalist and college wrestling legend Dan Gable the Presidential Medal of Freedom on Monday.

value.title: Joe Biden owes Philly $15,500 in unpaid bills after leaving a muddy mess from a campaign event. The city wants its money ASAP.
value.excerpt: Biden's team hasn't paid the $6,025 site fee for using Philly's FDR Park, and $9,500 to cover repairs of a portion of the park's waterlogged grounds.

value.title: Pence says US 'a week and a half away' from 'likely approval' of first coronavirus vaccine
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence said Friday that the U.S. is “maybe just a week and a half away” from the “likely approval” of the first vaccine to protect against the novel coronavirus.

value.title: Videos, virtual events and planned trips: Biden, Obama, Pence, Trump weigh in on Georgia runoffs
value.excerpt: President Trump, his predecessor and soon-to-be successor in the White House, as well as Vice President Mike Pence, are all weighing in on Georgia’s two Jan. 5 Senate runoff elections, where the Republican majority in the chamber is up for grabs.

value.title: Iowa's contact-tracing firm helped Trump, Reynolds campaigns
value.excerpt: After facing a workforce shortage for months, Iowa has awarded an emergency $2.3 million contact-tracing contract to a company owned by a Republican Party insider

value.title: Biden wrestles with politics in effort to depoliticize the Justice Department
value.excerpt: Political questions from Democrats and a new Republican litmus test have suddenly become complicating factors in one of President-elect Joe Biden's most critical choices: picking a new Attorney General to lead the Justice Department out of its highly politicized era.

value.title: In race to cement legacy, Trump pushes dozens of 'midnight regulations'
value.excerpt: The Trump administration is quietly racing to solidify its legacy, fulfill campaign promises and overhaul federal regulations that could take Joe Biden years to undo.

value.title: Republican congressman tells Trump to 'delete your account' after he tweeted a 45-minute speech repeating baseless voter-fraud claims
value.excerpt: Republican Rep. Adam Kinzinger, who represents Illinois' 16th District, quote-tweeted Trump on Thursday.

value.title: Trump, Pence to campaign in Georgia as Senate runoff turnout concerns grow among GOP
value.excerpt: Mike Pence and President Donald Trump's rallies for Georgia's senators will be against a backdrop of growing concerns about GOP turnout in the Senate runoff election.

value.title: Watters riffs on Biden choosing critics for Cabinet: 'They call him a buffoon, and he says "you get me'''
value.excerpt: "The Five" co-host Jesse Watters remarked Thursday that President-elect Joe Biden appears to have stocked his would-be Cabinet and administration with notable recent or former critics -- including Vice President-elect Sen.
